The '''Beast Spirit of Water''' (水のビーストスピリット ''Mizu no Bīsuto Supiritto''), also known as the '''Spirit of Water B''' (水のスピリットB ''Mizu no Supiritto Bī'') is one of the twenty [[Legendary Spirits]]. It contains the power of [[Ancient Mermaimon]] of the [[Warrior Ten]], and allows its user to evolve into the Beast Form [[Hybrid]] [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] [[Calamaramon]].

=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Frontier}}===
According to [[Baromon]], the Beast Spirit of Water is one of the Spirits that was given to [[Cherubimon (Frontier)|Cherubimon]] after the Warrior Ten defeated [[Lucemon (Frontier)|Lucemon]].{{rfe|DF|38|Endless Death Match! The Prelude of Lucemon's Revival}} However, it does not appear to have been in Cherubimon's possession as of when he turned evil and began his war, as it was instead hidden in a shipwreck at the bottom of the ocean, near an island. Because of this, [[Ranamon (Frontier)|Ranamon]] was the only one of the [[Evil Warriors]] to not originally possess a Beast Spirit (other than [[Kimura Kouichi|Duskmon]], because Cherubimon did not give him the [[Corrupted Beast Spirit of Darkness]] at first). Ranamon had her servants search for it across most of the [[Digital World]]'s landmasses, while she herself searched waterways, but none of them had any luck finding it.{{rfe|DF|15|Cool Beast Evolution! Calmaramon}}

When Ranamon learns that the [[Chosen Children]] have, after their defeat of [[Grottemon (Frontier)|Grottemon]], escaped to an island that she has not previously had searched for the Beast Spirit, she sends her [[Toucanmon]] fan club there to find it and also travels there herself. While fighting [[Orimoto Izumi]] (as [[Fairimon]]), she senses the Beast Spirit's presence nearby and dives underwater to find the shipwreck. The Beast Spirit reacts to her power of water, emerges from the shipwreck, and bonds itself to her, allowing her to [[Evolution#Digimon Frontier|Slide Evolve]] into Calamaramon. Ranamon has difficulty controlling the Beast Spirit, especially when she uses Calamaramon's {{ATO|Titanic Charge}} technique, as she often loses control of her flight path and is taken away from the fight.{{rfe|DF|15|Cool Beast Evolution! Calmaramon}} She continues to struggle to control it for some time.{{rfe|DF|16|Strength Does not Matter! The Beautiful Warrior, Shutumon}}

Izumi takes the Beast Spirit of Water, along with the [[Human Spirit of Water|Human Spirit]], when she defeats Ranamon/Calamaramon for the final time inside [[Sephirothmon]]'s Area of Water.{{rfe|DF|26|Ranamon's Tenacity! Female Digimon Personal Combat}}

The Beast Spirit of Water remains stored in Izumi's [[D-Scanner]] until the battle with Cherubimon at the [[Rose Morning Star]]. When [[Ofanimon (Frontier)|Ofanimon]] upgrades [[Kanbara Takuya]] and [[Minamoto Kouji]]'s D-Scanners, Izumi transfers both of the Spirits of Water to Kouji so that he can use them with eight other Spirits to Hyper Spirit Evolve into [[Magna Garurumon]].{{rfe|DF|35|Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!}}

In their last battles with Lucemon, the Chosen Children gain the ability to combine all twenty Spirits, including the Beast Spirit of Water, to become [[Susanoomon]].{{rfe|DF|48|Light and Darkness are One! Kouichi's Last Wish}}

