The '''Corrupted Beast Spirit of Darkness''' (闇のビーストスピリット ''Yami no Bīsuto Supiritto''), also known as the '''Spirit of Darkness B''' (闇のスピリットB ''Yami no Supiritto Bī'') is one of the twenty [[Legendary Spirits]].  It is an alternative form of the [[Beast Spirit of Darkness]], which contains the power of [[Ancient Sphinxmon]] of the [[Warrior Ten]], that has been transformed by [[Cherubimon]]'s magic.{{refd|Kaiser Leomon|kaiserleomon}}<ref name="basics">[https://digimon.net/profile/report014/ DigiBasics: "Hybrids" and "Spirits"]</ref> It allows its user to evolve into the Beast Form [[Hybrid]] [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] [[Velgrmon]].

=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Frontier}}===
When [[Cherubimon (Frontier)|Cherubimon]] turned [[Kimura Kouichi]] into [[Duskmon]], he did not give him the Corrupted Beast Spirit of Darkness at first. He only gives it to Duskmon when Kouchi/Duskmon, while fighting [[Minamoto Kouji]] (as [[Beowolfmon]]), recognizes Kouji as his brother and hesitates, allowing Kouji to overpower him. Cherubimon intervenes and decides that Kouichi's remaining human heart and feelings are a weakness, so he forces the Beast Spirit on Duskmon to Slide Evolve him into Velgrmon, to turn him into an immensely powerful "true Warrior of Darkness" who is bent on getting vengeance on Kouji for the hard life that he and their mother have lived.{{rfe|DF|30|Soaring! Warrior of Darkness Velgrmon}}{{rfe|DF|32|The Past is Revealed! Duskmon's Secret}}

With [[Kanbara Takuya]]'s assistance, Kouji (as Beowolfmon) defeats Duskmon/Velgrmon and scans the Corrupted Beast and [[Corrupted Human Spirit of Darkness|Human Spirits of Darkness]], along with the [[Human Spirit of Wood]],{{note|The [[Human Spirit of Wood]] is not seen on-screen or mentioned in ''[[Digimon Frontier - Episode 32|"The Past is Revealed! Duskmon's Secret"]]'', so [[Minamoto Kouji|Kouji]] is not seen physically taking it. That Kouji received it here is inferred based on [[Duskmon]] previously taking the Spirit in ''[[Digimon Frontier - Episode 20|"Mysterious Warrior Lurking in the Darkness, Duskmon!"]]'', and the Spirit later being depicted as in Kouji's possession in ''[[Digimon Frontier - Episode 35|"Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!"]]'' before he transfers it to [[Kanbara Takuya|Takuya]].|n="humanwood"}} freeing Kouichi from Cherubimon's control. The Corrupted Spirits are briefly stored in Kouji's [[D-Scanner]].{{rfe|DF|32|The Past is Revealed! Duskmon's Secret}}

When Kouichi stands up to Cherubimon, his confession of both his past hatred for Kouji and how meeting Kouji for real has changed him awakens the Spirits of Darkness, and they transform back into their true forms. Kouichi acquires a D-Scanner and the true Spirits of Darkness enter it, and he becomes able to Spirit Evolve into [[Löwemon]] and [[Kaiser Leomon]], instead of Duskmon and Velgrmon.{{rfe|DF|33|The New Warriors of Darkness! Löwemon & Kaiser Leomon}}

