Digicore.wikitext:
[[Image:Digicore.jpg|right|thumb|A diagram showing the location of [[Tyranomon]]'s Digicore.]]

A '''Digicore''' (デジコア ''Dejikoa''; Dub: ''DigiCore''), also referred to as a '''{{w|Kernel (computing)|computer kernel}}'''<ref name="DMArt" /> (電脳核 ''Den'noukaku''), is the controlling organ of a [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] that is said to be located in the center of a Digimon's body.{{refd|Mokumon}} Its functions correspond to the hearts{{refd|Candmon}} and brains of creatures from the real world,<ref name="DMArt">''Digital Monster - Artbook Ver.1～5&20th''</ref> and it is the Digimon analog of a soul.{{refd|Gulfmon}}{{refd|Orgemon (X-Antibody)|orgemon_x}} 

=Overview=
==Composition and function==
A Digicore is a program and data (a collection of numbers and symbols composed of {{w|binary code}}). The Digicore maintains the Digimon's vital functions, and as long as the Digicore itself is unharmed, the Digimon can keep functioning indefinitely regardless of what happens to the rest of its body.{{refd|Skull Mammon}} However, this means that any abnormalities or damage to its Digicore would be life-threatening to a Digimon, and if a Digimon loses its Digicore, it will be unable to maintain its vital functions and will immediately cease functioning.{{refd|Skull Mammon}}<ref>[http://digimon.net/city/gallery/p3/5-1.html ''Digimon Pendulum 3'': Skull Mammon]</ref> Because of this, Digicores are typically never left exposed, and are protected by skeletons, skin, and other features of a Digimon's body.<ref name="DMArt" /> The only Digimon who have exposed Digicores tend to be either the most powerful [[Ultimate]] Digimon (mounting them on the outside of their body, for instance because their body cannot contain their sheer power{{refd|Ultimate Chaosmon}}), or Digimon of the [[:Category:Undead Type|Undead Type]] (whose bodies have rotted to such an extent that their Digicores are visible).{{refd|Xuanwumon}}

Digicores are considered the defining feature of Digimon, so entities without Digicores, such as [[Death-X-mon]], cannot be classified as Digimon.{{refd|Death-X-mon|death-x-mon}} However, despite possessing a Digicore of its own, [[ZERO-ARMS: Grani]] is not classified as a Digimon.{{ref|''{{url2|https://twitter.com/yamaki_nyx/status/975591976249704448|Twitter: Chiaki J. Konaka, Mar 18, 2018, 9:37 PM status}}''}}

Digicores sometimes produce heat as a byproduct of functioning. The heat of a Digicore, and its effects on a Digimon's body, sometimes correlates with how passionate and exuberant the Digimon's temperament is. For example, [[Peti Meramon]]'s wild temperament causes its Digicore to burn intensely.{{refd|Peti Meramon}} This heat can have an impact on the Digimon's body. For example, the heat of [[Solarmon]]'s Digicore causes its metal body to be hot to the touch,{{refd|Solarmon}} and the intense burning of Peti Meramon's Digicore causes its entire body to be ablaze.{{refd|Peti Meramon}} The Digicores of some Digimon, such as [[Mechanorimon]], will overheat if the Digimon is overworked.{{refd|Mechanorimon}}

Similar to heat, the emotional strength of a Digicore can have an impact on a Digimon's performance. For example, [[Grappu Leomon]]'s turbines are driven by the fighting spirit emitted by its Digicore, and require significant emotional strength and fighting spirit to be run.{{refd|Grappu Leomon}}

In some cases, Digicores can also become weapons themselves, capitalizing on their vast amount of information that they contain.<sup>''[citation needed]''</sup>

==Life cycle and evolution==
The information in the Digicore is used to generate the physical body of the Digimon, so the percentage of particular elements within a Digicore determines what and how certain features are expressed in a Digimon and how they evolve, in addition to their pedigree. For example, [[Dramon]]-type Digimon (those that bear the "-dramon" suffix in their name) must possess Dragon-factor data in their Digicore; the higher the percentage of that data, the more the shape of their body becomes a Dragon-type.{{refd|Coredramon (Green)|coredramon_g}}{{refd|Coredramon (Blue)|coredramon_b}} Similarly, [[Gaioumon]] becomes [[Gaioumon: Itto Mode]] when latent oni data in its Digicore is awakened.{{refd|Gaioumon: Itto Mode|gaioumon_itto}}

Similarly, the size of a Digimon is determined by the amount of data and content embedded in their Digicore, and the size of the texture expressing their body.<ref name="DMArt" /> As such, that data may be subject to being unable to be completely rendered due to technological limitations, especially if it is extraordinary in size.{{refd|Examon}} 

When a Digimon reaches the end of its life span, it compresses and converts its own Digicore into a [[Digitama]], leaving behind its data to the next generation.<ref name="DMArt" />

When two Digimon undergo [[Jogress Evolution]], their Digicores are normally totally fused, resulting in a single new Digimon. If the process of Digicore fusion is left incomplete, the resulting Digimon maintains its form in a very unstable state.{{refd|Chaosmon}}{{refd|Chaosmon: Valdur Arm}}

The Digicores (souls) of sinners that fall into the [[Dark Area]] are cast into the sentient crimson flames, {{w|Gospel|El Evangelio}}, which impose judgment upon and offer salvation to them.{{refd|Beelzebumon (X-Antibody)|beelzebumon_x}} 

G-Cells invading Digicores can bring forth new evolutions, including [[Metal Greymon: "G" Erosion Mode]], [[Skull Greymon: "G" Erosion Mode]], [[Mugendramon: MFS-3 Mode‎]] and [[War Greymon: "G" Erosion Mode]].<ref>[[Digimon Con|Digimon Con 2025]]</ref><ref>''[https://p-bandai.jp/contents/item-pickup-godzilla-digimon/ "Digital Monster COLOR Godzilla 70th Edition" Planning Staff Interview]''</ref>

===X-Antibody===
To protect themselves against the effects of [[Program X]], Digimon of sufficient strength are able to alter their Digicores to incorporate Program X itself in the form of the [[X-Antibody]]. If X-Antibodies are concentrated within a Digicore at sufficient levels ("normal level" or "level 2"), they actively extract latent data from within the Digicore and use it to trigger [[Evolution#X-Antibody and Evolution|X-Evolution]], transforming the Digimon into a form that expresses that latent data.{{ref|http://web.archive.org/web/20090310002240/http://www.digimon.channel.or.jp/chronicle/ndw-03.html}}

X-Evolution can have a variety of effects on a Digimon's appearance and power, all depending on what and how much latent data there is to extract from the Digicore. As such, if the Digimon in question has already naturally manifested its latent abilities, than the X-Antibody won't have much effect on it and its appearance won't change much.{{refd|Goddramon (X-Antibody)|goddramon_x}}{{refd|Holydramon (X-Antibody)|holydramon_x}}

Some Digimon can force the X-Antibody within their Digicores to keep their body functioning even after they have died, in a process called [[Evolution#X-Antibody and Evolution|Death-X-Evolution]].{{ref|''{{url|https://web.archive.org/web/20090126194928/http://www.digimon.channel.or.jp:80/chronicle/30/ch-03.html|Digimon Chronicle: Death-X Evolution}}''}} Death-X-Evolved Digimon of the [[Prototype Digimon#DORU Series|DORU Series]] in particular instinctively hunt the Digicores of other Digimon in order to keep their bodies animated.{{refd|Death-X-DORUgamon}}{{refd|Death-X-DORUguremon}}{{refd|Death-X-DORUgoramon}} [[Death-X-DORUguremon]] specifically hunts for massive Digicores so that it can evolve.{{refd|Death-X-DORUguremon}}

==Special cases==
Demon-species Digimon characteristicaly have Digicores in which intense dark powers are concentrated. Such Digicores are called '''Darkcores''' (ダークコア, ''Dākukoa'').{{refd|Skull Satamon}}

Unlike any other Digimon species, the [[Four Holy Beasts]] and [[Huanglongmon]] each have twelve Digicores that orbit their bodies.{{refd|Xuanwumon}}{{refd|Baihumon}}{{refd|Huanglongmon}} In [[Baihumon]]'s case, these external Digicores manifest its immortality and immense power.{{refd|Baihumon}}

Instead of a physical body, [[Mokumon]] conceals its Digicore within a thick cloud of smoke. Since the smoke is generated by the very thing that the smoke is trying to protect, Mokumon is unique in that sense.{{refd|Mokumon}}{{ref|{{url2|http://web.archive.org/web/20100612132428/http://digimon.net/city/gallery/p3/1-1.html|''Digimon Pendulum 3'': Mokumon}}}}

[[Candmon]] is unusual in that its Digicore is not contained within its body, but is instead mounted on the wick on its head, covered in flames. The flames correspond to the healthy function of the Digicore, so if they stop burning, Candmon's vital functions cease. However, it is theorized that the Digicore and flames are the full extent of Candmon's actual body, and that everything else is just a dummy.{{refd|Candmon}}

[[Prototype Digimon]] that originate from before Digimon were discovered have an outdated [[Digicore Interface]] on their brow, which allows them to reconfigure the data within their Digicores for such experiments. However, mistakes or carelessness made when reconfiguring the Digicore through the Interface can have devastating effects on the Digicore, even causing it to cease to function in the worst case scenario, so Interfaces are generally no longer used. However, if a Digimon with an Interface receives the X-Antibody, they can use the Digicore Interface to unleash the latent data hidden in the deepest parts of their Digicore.{{ref|''{{url|web.archive.org/web/20070329111106/http://www.digimon.channel.or.jp/chronicle/dm-01.html|Digimon Chronicle: Prototype Digimon and the Digicore Interface}}''}} In some cases, the Digicore's very own creativity can be released through the Interface as well, causing new Digimon to be born from the "daydream of a Digicore".{{refd|Ouryumon}}{{refd|DORUgoramon}}

[[Skull Baluchimon]]'s Digicore constantly emits a cold, black vapor.{{refd|Skull Baluchimon}}

[[Sanzomon]] has accumulated the pure energy necessary to attain enlightenment in its Digicore. It is hunted by greedy Digimon who want to take this energy from its Digicore, as it is rumored that stealing this energy will confer immortality and heal injuries and terminal illness.{{refd|Sanzomon}}

[[Mugendramon]] and [[Chaosdramon]]'s Digicores are infected with different versions of a malicious program. As a result, Mugendramon is supplied with infinite power by its Digicore,{{refd|Mugendramon}} and the program in Chaosdramon's Digicore automatically implements improvements to make it even more destructive.{{refd|Chaosdramon}}

[[Dukemon: Crimson Mode]]'s Digicore is mounted on its breastplate. The [[Digital Hazard]] is sealed inside its Digicore.{{refd|Dukemon: Crimson Mode}}

[[Chaosmon]] is the result of an incomplete Jogress Evolution where the Digicores of the constituent Digimon failed to completely fuse. It has two Digicores that remain completely separate, which makes it unstable and short-lived.{{refd|Chaosmon}}{{refd|Chaosmon: Valdur Arm}} [[Ultimate Chaosmon]] is both the result of an incomplete Jogress and an extremely powerful Ultimate Digimon, so it is unable to store its two Digicores within its body. As a result, its Digicores manifest bare.{{refd|Ultimate Chaosmon}}

Being a Demon Lord type, [[Beelzebumon]]'s Digicore would, under ordinary circumstances, be consumed by El Evangelio once it is consigned to the Dark Area, However, having assimilated the X-Antibody into its body, [[Beelzebumon (X-Antibody)]] is able to suppress the will of El Evangelio without incurring the wrath of the flames.{{refd|Beelzebumon (X-Antibody)|beelzebumon_x}}

[[Avenge Kidmon]] is the result of the Minus Mind Data overloading the Digicore of a Digimon who had been defeated by [[Magna Kidmon]]. This caused it to mutate into a form that strongly resembles Magna Kidmon.{{refd|Avenge Kidmon}}

[[Mitamamon]]'s Digicore is ordinarily its only tangible, physical substance, since the rest of its body is an agglomeration of elemental energies. Those who find its Digicore within the rest of its body become able to touch the body itself.{{refd|Mitamamon}}

Because [[Erlangmon: Blast Mode]]'s third eye is also its Digicore, it can be considered to be a dangerous form whose overwhelming strength comes at the expense of its Digicore being virtually exposed.{{refd|Erlangmon: Blast Mode}}

In ''[[Digimon Dreamers]]'', some Digimon possess special Digicores, allowing them to draw upon their power for far greater feats than a Digimon of the same species with a normal Digicore. This includes [[Wizarmon (Dreamers)|Wizarmon]], who can use it for the legendary electric attack, {{ATO|Bolt Break}}{{ref|''[[Pulse-21|Digimon Dreamers: "The World of 0 and 1"]]''}} and [[Pal]], who, as [[Bulkmon]], can freely manipulate electricity, form it into wings, and perform the {{ATO|Core Electrical Fist}} attack.{{ref|''[[Pulse-23|Digimon Dreamers: "A Dream to Evolve"]]''}}

