=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Adventure 02}}===
Toward the end of the series, [[Qinglongmon (Adventure)|Qinglongmon]] shares the power of its Digicores with the [[Chosen Children]] to grant their [[partner Digimon]] the ability to [[Evolution|evolve]] into higher forms.

In ''[[Digimon Adventure 02 - Episode 39|"Everyone Advance Out! Imperialdramon"]]'', [[Gennai]] arrives in the Real World and presents the Chosen Children (except [[Tachikawa Mimi]]) with one of Qinglongmon's Digicores. When it shines in response to their [[Digivice]]s:

* [[Motomiya Daisuke]] and [[Ichijouji Ken]]'s [[Paildramon]] gains the ability to Ultimate Evolve into [[Imperialdramon: Dragon Mode|Imperialdramon]].
* [[Yagami Taichi]]'s [[Agumon (Adventure)|Agumon]], [[Ishida Yamato]]'s [[Gabumon (Adventure)|Gabumon]], [[Takenouchi Sora]]'s [[Piyomon (Adventure)|Piyomon]], [[Izumi Koushirou]]'s [[Tentomon (Adventure)|Tentomon]], [[Kido Jou]]'s [[Gomamon (Adventure)|Gomamon]], [[Takaishi Takeru]]'s [[Patamon (Adventure)|Patamon]], and [[Yagami Hikari]]'s [[Tailmon (Adventure)|Tailmon]] all regain the ability to Super Evolve to the [[Perfect]] level. In ''[[Digimon Adventure 02 - Episode 43|"Invasion of the Demon Army"]]'', the Digimon all give up this power and pass it on to Imperialdramon, giving it the ability to Mode Change into [[Imperialdramon: Fighter Mode]].
* Daisuke's [[V-mon (Adventure)|V-mon]], Ken's [[Wormmon (Adventure)|Wormmon]], [[Inoue Miyako]]'s [[Hawkmon (Adventure)|Hawkmon]], and [[Hida Iori]]'s [[Armadimon (Adventure)|Armadimon]] all begin to remain in their [[Child]] forms by default while in the Real World, instead of reverting to their [[Baby II]] forms.

In ''[[Digimon Adventure 02 - Episode 40|"The Great Free-for-all Fight in New York and Hong Kong!"]]'', [[Benjamin]] (Gennai's North American counterpart) takes a sample of the power of Qinglongmon's Digicore from Daisuke's [[D-3]] to restore Mimi's [[Palmon (Adventure)|Palmon's]] ability to Super Evolve as well.

Since the power of Qinglongmon's Digicores (which had already been weakened before) is intended to maintain the balance of the Digital World itself, sharing this power causes the Digital World to fall into ruin. In ''[[Digimon Adventure 02 - Episode 46|"Black War Greymon vs War Greymon"]]'', Qinglongmon once again shares some of its Digicore power with Agumon to restore his ability to Warp Evolve into [[War Greymon]], so that he can fight [[Black War Greymon (Adventure)|Black War Greymon]].

