==Novel==
==={{hdr|Digimon Seekers}}===
The Digicore is the data center of a Digimon’s core. It is the core of life, the area that shows the Digimon as an individual — the ego or the soul of a Digimon.

Using Mind Link with a [[Digimon Linker]] separates the users' consciousness from their body and sends its data to the Digicore of a Digimon, thus allowing them to fully interact with the Digital World with their five senses.

==Video Games==
==={{hdr|Digimon World Re:Digitize}} and {{hdr|Digimon World Re:Digitize Decode|Decode}}===
After [[Digimaru]] dies, its core can be transferred to a new [[Digitama]] so it inherits some of its powers.

Mysterious Digicores are items that can be traded to [[Hagurumon]] in the [[Village of Beginnings]] for [[DigiMemory (Xros Wars)|DigiMemory]] recharges.

After [[Lucemon|Lucemon's]] death in the Digitower, his purple Digicore is left behind. It curses [[Barbamon]], then rises, breaking through the ceiling and heading to the upper leaves of the Digitower. After being killed as [[Lucemon: Satan Mode]], his Digicore becomes golden, and is then reborn as Lucemon.

After [[Taiga]] and [[Kuga Yuuya]] defeat [[Yggdrasill_7D6]], [[Plotmon (Re:Digitize)|Plotmon (X-Antibody)]] brings [[DORUmon (X-evolution)|DORUmon's]] Digicore, the Blank Digicore, to Taiga, so Digimaru can become the same type of Digimon as he was and become a good [[Partner Digimon]]. This unlocks [[Alphamon]] as an [[Evolution/Video_Games#Digimon_World_Re:Digitize_.26_Decode|evolution]] for Digimaru. Said Blank Digicore can then be traded to [[Agumon (X-Antibody)]] for a Jet-Black Magic Circle.
