The '''Human Spirit of Earth''' (土のヒューマンスピリット ''Tsuchi no Hyūman Supiritto''), also known as the '''Spirit of Earth H''' (土のスピリットH ''Tsuchi no Supiritto Eichi'') is one of the twenty [[Legendary Spirits]]. It contains the power of [[Ancient Volcamon]] of the [[Warrior Ten]], and allows its user to evolve into the Human Form [[Hybrid]] [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] [[Grottemon]].

=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Frontier}}===
According to [[Baromon]], the Human Spirit of Earth is one of the Spirits that was given to [[Cherubimon (Frontier)|Cherubimon]] after the Warrior Ten defeated [[Lucemon (Frontier)|Lucemon]].{{rfe|DF|38|Endless Death Match! The Prelude of Lucemon's Revival}} When Cherubimon turned evil and began his war, he used the Human Spirit of Earth to create Grottemon as one of the [[Evil Warriors]].{{rfe|DF|31|Decisive Battle!! Rose of Venus, Ofanimon's Rescue Plan}}

When [[Kanbara Takuya]] (as [[Vritramon]]) defeats Grottemon (as [[Gigasmon]]) for the first time, Grottemon's Human Spirit of Earth is exposed with his [[DigiCode]], along with the other Spirits in his possession (the [[Beast Spirit of Earth]], [[Human Spirit of Wind]], and [[Human Spirit of Ice]]). Takuya takes the Beast Spirit of Earth and returns the Human Spirit of Ice to [[Himi Tomoki]], but Grottemon recovers and runs away with the Human Spirits of Earth and Wind.{{rfe|DF|12|Roar, Vritramon! Defeat Gigasmon!}}

[[Shibayama Junpei]] takes the Human Spirit of Earth when he (as [[Bolgmon]]) defeats Grottomon for the final time. He also recovers the Human Spirit of Wind and returns it to [[Orimoto Izumi]].{{rfe|DF|14|Thunder! Even Rock Breaks! Bolgmon's Do-or-Die Challenge}}

The Human Spirit of Earth remains stored in Junpei's [[D-Scanner]] until the battle with Cherubimon at the [[Venus Rose]]. During the battle, Cherubimon subdues Junpei and takes his D-Scanner, along with all the Spirits in it, but [[Ofanimon (Frontier)|Ofanimon]] steals all of the D-Scanners and Spirits back under the pretense of purifying Cherubimon and returns them to the Chosen Children. When Ofanimon upgrades Takuya's D-Scanner, Junpei transfers the Human Spirit of Earth to Takuya so that he can use it with nine other Spirits to Hyper Spirit Evolve into [[Kaiser Greymon]].{{rfe|DF|35|Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!}}

When the [[Chosen Children]] visit the [[Village of Beginnings]], the Human Spirit of Earth reacts to the presence of the [[DigiTama]] of the Digimon who Cherubimon had used to create Grottemon. During their fight to protect the Village from the [[Royal Knights]], the DigiTama calls the Spirit out of Takuya's D-Scanner and uses it to reincarnate as Grottemon, this time an ally of the Chosen Children, and the other Human Spirits of the former Evil Warriors do the same. The Chosen Children use their Human Spirits and the ten Warriors attack the Royal Knights together, but the Royal Knights escape and destroy the Village. Afterwards, Grottemon dissolves and the Human Spirit is returned to Takuya.{{rfe|DF|42|Protect the Digitama! The Miracle of Disappearing Life}}

In their last battles with Lucemon, the Chosen Children gain the ability to combine all twenty Spirits, including the Human Spirit of Earth, to become [[Susanoomon]].{{rfe|DF|48|Light and Darkness are One! Kouichi's Last Wish}}
