The '''Human Spirit of Light''' (光のヒューマンスピリット ''Hikari no Hyūman Supiritto''), also known as the '''Spirit of Light H''' (光のスピリットH ''Hikari no Supiritto Eichi'') is one of the twenty [[Legendary Spirits]]. It contains the power of [[Ancient Garurumon]] of the [[Warrior Ten]], and allows its user to evolve into the Human Form [[Hybrid]] [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] [[Wolfmon]]. 

=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Frontier}}===
According to [[Baromon]], the Human Spirit of Light is one of the Spirits that was given to [[Seraphimon (Frontier)|Seraphimon]] after the Warrior Ten defeated [[Lucemon (Frontier)|Lucemon]].{{rfe|DF|38|Endless Death Match! The Prelude of Lucemon's Revival}} When [[Cherubimon (Frontier)|Cherubimon]] turned evil and began his war, the Beast Spirit of Light was hidden in a pit in the labyrinth under [[Fire Terminal]]. Seraphimon had told [[Ofanimon (Frontier)|Ofanimon]] where he had hidden the Spirit.{{rfe|DF|34|Decisive Battle!! Rose Morning Star, Ophanimon's Rescue Plan}}

When [[Minamoto Kouji]] arrives in Fire Terminal, Ofanimon instructs him to collect the Spirits and guides him to the Human Spirit of Light with a compass on his [[D-Scanner]]. The compass brings him to the labyrinth chamber where the pit is, just as the [[Pagumon]] are chasing [[Shibayama Junpei]] and [[Himi Tomoki]] there. During his fight with the Pagumon and the [[Raremon]] that one of them evolves into, Kouji is knocked into the pit, where the Human Spirit of Light reveals itself to him and chooses him as its wielder. Kouji scans the Spirit and uses it to [[Evolution#Digimon Frontier|Spirit Evolve]] into [[Wolfmon]] and fight Raremon.{{rfe|DF|02|Wolfmon of Light, The Underground Labyrinth Battle!}}

Kouji continues to use the Spirit throughout the series. During his second fight with [[Kimura Kouichi|Duskmon]], Seraphimon's [[DigiTama]] releases some of its power to enable Kouji to combine the Human Spirit with the [[Beast Spirit of Light]] to become [[Beowolfmon]].{{rfe|DF|27|Double Spirit Miracle! Beowolfmon is Born}} 

During the battle against Cherubimon at the [[Rose Morning Star]], Cherubimon subdues Kouji and takes his D-Scanner, along with all the Spirits in it, but Ofanimon steals all of the D-Scanners and Spirits back under the pretense of purifying Cherubimon and returns them to the Chosen Children. When Ofanimon upgrades Kouji's D-Scanner, he becomes able to use this Spirit with nine other Spirits to Hyper Spirit Evolve into [[Magna Garurumon]].{{rfe|DF|35|Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!}}

In their last battles with Lucemon, the Chosen Children gain the ability to combine all twenty Spirits, including the Human Spirit of Light, to become [[Susanoomon]].{{rfe|DF|48|Light and Darkness are One! Kouichi's Last Wish}}

