The '''Human Spirit of Steel''' (鋼のヒューマンスピリット ''Hagane no Hyūman Supiritto''), also known as the '''Spirit of Steel H''' (鋼のスピリットH ''Hagane no Supiritto Eichi'') is one of the twenty [[Legendary Spirits]]. It contains the power of [[Ancient Wisemon]] of the [[Warrior Ten]], and allows its user to evolve into the Human Form [[Hybrid]] [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] [[Mercuremon]].

=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Frontier}}===
According to [[Baromon]], the Human Spirit of Steel is one of the Spirits that was given to [[Cherubimon (Frontier)|Cherubimon]] after the Warrior Ten defeated [[Lucemon (Frontier)|Lucemon]].{{rfe|DF|38|Endless Death Match! The Prelude of Lucemon's Revival}} When Cherubimon turned evil and began his war, he used the Human Spirit of Steel to create Mercuremon as one of the [[Evil Warriors]].{{rfe|DF|31|Decisive Battle!! Rose Morning Star, Ofanimon's Rescue Plan}}

[[Kanbara Takuya]] (as [[Aldamon]]) takes the Human Spirit of Steel when he defeats Mercuremon for the first time inside Mercuremon's [[Sephirothmon]] form. However, Mercuremon continues to exist for a while longer as Sephirothmon using the [[Beast Spirit of Steel]], which Takuya is not given the opportunity to take at this point.{{rfe|DF|28|Takuya's Fusion Evolution, Aldamon's Explosive Attack}}

The Human Spirit of Steel remains stored in Takuya's [[D-Scanner]] until the battle with Cherubimon at the [[Rose Morning Star]]. During the battle, Cherubimon subdues Takuya and takes his D-Scanner, along with all the Spirits in it, but [[Ofanimon (Frontier)|Ofanimon]] steals all of the D-Scanners and Spirits back under the pretense of purifying Cherubimon and returns them to the Chosen Children. When Ofanimon upgrades Takuya and [[Minamoto Kouji]]'s D-Scanner, Takuya transfers the Human Spirit of Steel to Kouji so that he can use it with nine other Spirits to Hyper Spirit Evolve into [[Magna Garurumon]].{{rfe|DF|35|Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!}}

When the [[Chosen Children]] visit the [[Village of Beginnings]], the Human Spirit of Steel reacts to the presence of the [[DigiTama]] of the Digimon who Cherubimon had used to create Mercuremon. During their fight to protect the Village from the [[Royal Knights]], the DigiTama calls the Spirit out of Kouji's D-Scanner and uses it to reincarnate as Mercuremon, this time an ally of the Chosen Children, and the other Human Spirits of the former Evil Warriors do the same. The Chosen Children use their Human Spirits and the ten Warriors attack the Royal Knights together, but the Royal Knights escape and destroy the Village. Afterwards, Mercuremon dissolves and the Human Spirit is returned to Kouji.{{rfe|DF|42|Protect the Digitama! The Miracle of Disappearing Life}}

In their last battles with Lucemon, the Chosen Children gain the ability to combine all twenty Spirits, including the Human Spirit of Steel, to become [[Susanoomon]].{{rfe|DF|48|Light and Darkness are One! Kouichi's Last Wish}}
