The '''Human Spirit of Wood''' (木のヒューマンスピリット ''Ki no Hyūman Supiritto''), also known as the '''Spirit of Wood H''' (木のスピリットH ''Ki no Supiritto Eichi'') is one of the twenty [[Legendary Spirits]]. It contains the power of [[Ancient Troiamon]] of the [[Warrior Ten]], and allows its user to evolve into the Human Form [[Hybrid]] [[Digimon (species)|Digimon]] [[Arbormon]].

=Appearances=
==Anime==
==={{hdr|Digimon Frontier}}===
According to [[Baromon]], the Human Spirit of Wood is one of the Spirits that was given to [[Cherubimon (Frontier)|Cherubimon]] after the Warrior Ten defeated [[Lucemon (Frontier)|Lucemon]].{{rfe|DF|38|Endless Death Match! The Prelude of Lucemon's Revival}} When Cherubimon turned evil and began his war, he used the Human Spirit of Wood to create Arbormon as one of the [[Evil Warriors]].{{rfe|DF|34|Decisive Battle!! Rose Morning Star, Ofanimon's Rescue Plan}}

After the [[Chosen Children]] defeat Arbormon and take his [[Beast Spirit of Wood]], [[Kimura Kouichi|Duskmon]] finishes Arbormon off and takes his Human Spirit.{{rfe|DF|20|Mysterious Warrior Lurking in the Darkness, Duskmon!}} [[Minamoto Kouji]] takes the Spirit, along with Duskmon's own corrupted Spirit of Darkness, when he (as [[Beowolfmon]]) defeats Duskmon.{{rfe|DF|32|The Past is Revealed! Duskmon's Secret}}{{note|The Human Spirit of Wood is not seen on-screen or mentioned in ''[[Digimon Frontier - Episode 32|"The Past is Revealed! Duskmon's Secret"]]'', so [[Minamoto Kouji|Kouji]] is not seen physically taking it. That Kouji received it here is inferred based on [[Duskmon]] previously taking the Spirit in ''[[Digimon Frontier - Episode 20|"Mysterious Warrior Lurking in the Darkness, Duskmon!"]]'', and the Spirit later being depicted as in Kouji's possession in ''[[Digimon Frontier - Episode 35|"Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!"]]'' before he transfers it to [[Kanbara Takuya|Takuya]].|n="humanwood"}} 

The Human Spirit of Wood remains stored in Kouji's [[D-Scanner]] until the battle with Cherubimon at the [[Rose Morning Star]]. During the battle, Cherubimon subdues Kouji and takes his D-Scanner, along with all the Spirits in it, but [[Ofanimon (Frontier)|Ofanimon]] steals all of the D-Scanners and Spirits back under the pretense of purifying Cherubimon and returns them to the Chosen Children. When Ofanimon upgrades Takuya and Kouji's D-Scanners, Kouji transfers both of the Spirits of Wood to Takuya so that he can use them with eight other Spirits to Hyper Spirit Evolve into [[Kaiser Greymon]].{{rfe|DF|35|Spirits Become One! Takuya and Kouji's Ultimate Evolution!}}

When the [[Chosen Children]] visit the [[Village of Beginnings]], the Human Spirit of Wood reacts to the presence of the [[DigiTama]] of the Digimon who Cherubimon had used to create Arbormon. During their fight to protect the Village from the [[Royal Knights]], the DigiTama calls the Spirit out of Takuya's D-Scanner and uses it to reincarnate as Arbormon, this time an ally of the Chosen Children, and the other Human Spirits of the former Evil Warriors do the same. The Chosen Children use their Human Spirits and the ten Warriors attack the Royal Knights together, but the Royal Knights escape and destroy the Village. Afterwards, Arbormon dissolves and the Human Spirit is returned to Takuya.{{rfe|DF|42|Protect the Digitama! The Miracle of Disappearing Life}}

In their last battles with Lucemon, the Chosen Children gain the ability to combine all twenty Spirits, including the Human Spirit of Wood, to become [[Susanoomon]].{{rfe|DF|48|Light and Darkness are One! Kouichi's Last Wish}}

