|p=Digimon Reference Book
|e=A Puppet Digimon that took in data from {{w|karakuri puppet}}s, traditional Japanese crafts. Characterized by the large {{w|sakazuki}} it wears on its head and its long, beautiful black hair, it has an appearance that resembles a beautiful woman at first glance, but beneath its kimono is a mechanical karakuri puppet. It has been seen living together with groups of [[Kokeshimon]] in large, old castles and mansions in the [[Digital World: Shambala|Eastern Digital World]], and the sight of them makes them look just like sisters.{{br}}It conceals a multitude of mechanical arms and weapons beneath its elegant kimono, and also has a side like an assassin where it tenaciously hunts its prey, contrary to its calm demeanor. When hunting its target, it deploys the wheels on its legs and its mechanical arms, and corners the enemy with a hideous look, baring its fangs from its gaping mouth.{{br}}Its Special Moves are skillfully mincing the enemy with the arms and weapons beneath its kimono ({{j2|{{AT|Karakuri Enbu:}} {{AT|w=Hachikazuki}}|Corpse-reeling Bewitching Dance: Hachikazuki}}), and dousing the enemy with the strong acid in its bowl, causing them to melt ({{AT|Hatsuse no Omotenashi|Hatsuse Hospitality}}).
|j=日本の伝統工芸であるからくり人形のデータを取り込んだパペット型デジモン。頭に被った大きな盃（さかずき）と長く美しい黒髪が特徴的で、一見すれば美しい女性のような姿をしているが、着物の下は機械じかけのからくり人形である。東方のデジタルワールドに存在する大きな古城や屋敷で、コケシモンたちと共に暮らしている姿が目撃されており、その光景はさながら姉妹のようにも見える。<br>　美しい着物の下には複数のからくり腕と武器を隠し持っており、物静かな佇まいとは裏腹に強かに獲物を狩る暗殺者のような側面も持つ。標的を狩る際には脚部の車輪とからくり腕を展開し、裂けるように開いた口から牙を剥き出しにしたおぞましい表情で敵を追い詰める。<br>　必殺技は、着物の下の腕と武器で鮮やかに敵を斬り刻む『{{ATK|骸繰艶舞・鉢かづき}}』（からくりえんぶはちかづき）と、椀の中の強酸を相手にぶちまけて溶かしてしまう『{{ATK|初瀬のおもてなし}}』。
|u=karakurumon
|ety={{JP}} {{ETY|Karakuru}} <br>{{verb}} From {{ETY|Karakuru}} {{ETYK|絡繰る|r={{FGM|からくる}}}} meaning "to pull, stretch, and move a thread".
